  "response_text": "# Exercise While Fasting\n\nYes, you can, but there are tradeoffs to consider:\n\n## Potential benefits\n- May enhance fat burning for some people\n- Can fit schedules better\n- Some find it energizing\n\n## Potential drawbacks\n- Less fuel available means reduced performance/endurance\n- Increased fatigue or dizziness\n- May increase muscle breakdown\n- Harder to sustain intense workouts\n\n## What works best depends on:\n- **Type of exercise** — Light cardio or yoga may be fine; heavy lifting or intense cardio is harder fasted\n- **Your goals** — Building muscle typically needs fuel; fat loss is more flexible\n- **Individual tolerance** — Some people feel fine, others don't\n- **Fast duration** — Short fasts (12-16 hours) are easier than longer ones\n\n## Practical tips\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat something shortly after\n- Start with shorter/lighter sessions to see how you feel\n- Break the fast if you feel unwell\n\nMost evidence suggests eating *before* intense exercise improves performance, but light activity while fasting is generally safe for most people. Listen to your body and adjust based on how you feel.",
